<noinclude>
根據1947年起修訂並實施的《皇室典範》，皇位只限由皇族男性以及後裔繼承<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kunaicho.go.jp/e-kunaicho/hourei-01.html |title=存档副本 |access-date=2019-05-17 |archive-date=2012-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121127182858/http://www.kunaicho.go.jp/e-kunaicho/hourei-01.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>；但是[[平成|平成]]時代前期，[[天皇|天皇]][[明仁|明仁]]的兩名嫡子（長子[[德仁|皇太子德仁親王]]、次子秋篠宮文仁親王）都長期只有女兒，皇室已有四十一年沒有其他可繼承皇位的男性後裔出生，因此悠仁親王在2006年的誕生，使當時醞釀修改《皇室典範》的行動很快就被擱置。<ref name="cnn-birth">{{cite news | url = http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/asiapcf/09/05/japan.princess/index.html | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20081211040020/http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/asiapcf/09/05/japan.princess/index.html | archivedate = 11 December 2008 | publisher = CNN | title = Japan's Princess Kiko has boy | date = 6 September 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/5320224.stm|title=Japan succession debate to go on|last=Hogg|first=Chris|date=6 September 2006|publisher=BBC News|location=Tokyo|accessdate=2019-05-17|archive-date=2021-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125002823/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/5320224.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="asahi">女性天皇容認68%に、朝日新聞、2009年3月22日</ref>

此後幾年，[[三笠宮崇仁親王|三笠宮崇仁親王]]、[[寬仁親王|寬仁親王]]與[[桂宮宜仁親王|桂宮宜仁親王]]等先後過世，皇位繼承人從7人又降到3人<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1293147-20161027.htm|title=日本崇仁親王逝世　享年101歲|publisher=[[香港電台|香港電台]]|date=2016-10-27|accessdate=2016-10-27|archive-date=2016-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027125841/http://news.rthk.hk/rthk/ch/component/k2/1293147-20161027.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tw.news.yahoo.com/%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E5%AF%AC%E4%BB%81%E8%A6%AA%E7%8E%8B%E9%80%9D%E4%B8%96-%E4%BA%AB%E5%B9%B466-083508297.html |title=日本寬仁親王逝世 享年66 |access-date=2019-05-17 |archive-date=2020-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126030032/https://tw.news.yahoo.com/%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E5%AF%AC%E4%BB%81%E8%A6%AA%E7%8E%8B%E9%80%9D%E4%B8%96-%E4%BA%AB%E5%B9%B466-083508297.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>；幾位皇室女性也因為下嫁而依法脫離皇室。<ref>{{cite news|title=Wedding Bells to Ring for Japanese Princess|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/japanrealtime/2014/05/27/wedding-bells-to-ring-for-japanese-princess/|newspaper=Wall Street Journal Japan|accessdate=2019-05-17|archive-date=2019-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520162019/https://blogs.wsj.com/japanrealtime/2014/05/27/wedding-bells-to-ring-for-japanese-princess/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-royals/japanese-princess-ayako-gives-up-royal-status-to-marry-commoner-idUSKCN1N310V|title=Japanese Princess Ayako gives up royal status to marry commoner|publisher=Reuters|date=29 October 2018|accessdate=30 October 2018|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205125052/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-royals/japanese-princess-ayako-gives-up-royal-status-to-marry-commoner-idUSKCN1N310V|dead-url=no}}</ref>在不修訂《皇室典範》的情況下，為了允許[[天皇明仁退位|天皇明仁退位]]，2017年新訂的特別法裡，同時要求日本政府討論皇族女性婚後仍保有皇族身分的可行性，但不涉及其皇位繼承權。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4812193/japan-emperor-akihito-abdicate//|title=Japan Will Allow Emperor Akihito to Step Down, the Country's First Abdication in 200 Years|last=Kilpatrick|first=Ryan|publisher=Time Inc.|date=June 8, 2017|website=time.com|access-date=August 3, 2017|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928102031/https://time.com/4812193/japan-emperor-akihito-abdicate/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

